title: Give notice of your intention to oppose a trade mark

heading_context: Give notice of your intention to oppose a trade mark
chunks.html_content:
Tell Intellectual Property Office you intend to oppose a trade mark application, sometimes known as giving ‘notice of threatened opposition’. This will give you one extra month to file your opposition.

You must apply in the 2 months after the trade mark application is first published in the online trade marks journal.

You’ll need to know:

  • the trade mark application number
  • whether it’s a UK or International (UK) application
  • one of the trade mark classes applied for
